# Auto: BSL Standards

Apply when editing or reviewing BSL/OneScript/SDBL files.

## Structure

- Business logic belongs in common modules, object/manager modules or processing modules; form module is a thin UI layer.
- Use Russian –С–°–Я-style regions. Do not create pseudo-regions via comments.
- Public exported procedures/functions go to `#–Ю–±–ї–∞—Б—В—М –Я—А–Њ–≥—А–∞–Љ–Љ–љ—Л–є–Ш–љ—В–µ—А—Д–µ–є—Б`.
- Internal helpers go to `#–Ю–±–ї–∞—Б—В—М –°–ї—Г–ґ–µ–±–љ—Л–µ–Я—А–Њ—Ж–µ–і—Г—А—Л–Ш–§—Г–љ–Ї—Ж–Є–Є`.
- Avoid regions inside procedures/functions.

## Client/server

- `&–Э–∞–Ъ–ї–Є–µ–љ—В–µ`: UI, current row, notifications, command handlers; no DB queries.
- `&–Э–∞–°–µ—А–≤–µ—А–µ–С–µ–Ј–Ъ–Њ–љ—В–µ–Ї—Б—В–∞`: DB queries, writes, heavy logic; pass parameters explicitly.
- `&–Э–∞–°–µ—А–≤–µ—А–µ`: only when form context is required.
- Do not call server from client inside loops.

## Code style

- One statement per line.
- Prefer early return over deep nesting.
- Do not compare booleans to `–Ш—Б—В–Є–љ–∞`/`–Ы–Њ–ґ—М`.
- Avoid `?(...)` in project code unless explicitly approved.
- Do not use `–Т—Л–њ–Њ–ї–љ–Є—В—М()` / `–Т—Л—З–Є—Б–ї–Є—В—М()` without a documented reason.
- Do not concatenate user input into queries.
- Do not store credentials in code.

## Data operations

- Use parameterized queries.
- Batch operations where possible.
- Check rights, locks, posting behavior and change prohibition dates when business data can be affected.
- For complex return values use `–°—В—А—Г–Ї—В—Г—А–∞` with explicit keys such as `–£—Б–њ–µ—Е`, `–Ґ–µ–Ї—Б—В–Ю—И–Є–±–Ї–Є`, `–Ф–∞–љ–љ—Л–µ`.

## Verification

After BSL changes, run available validation: syntaxcheck / check_1c_code / review_1c_code / BSL LS / project tests. If unavailable, use a manual checklist and report the limitation.

